U.S. Consumers Expect to Spend Less on Technology

-- B y   A l e x   T a n z i
-- 
2011-09-27T13:13:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-27/u-s-consumers-expect-to-spend-less-on-technology-table-.html
Consumer expectations about the economy
weakened in Sept. according to the CEA-CNET Index of Consumer Expectations.  Consumer expectations for technology spending over the next year
fell to 81.9 in Sept. from 84.4 a month earlier. The index is formulated
from a 1,000 person telephone survey.  Following is a table of consumer expectations for technology:  
